
[1]eucharist

   EU'CHARIST, n. [Gr. a giving of thanks; well, favor.]

   1. The sacrament of the Lord's supper; the solemn act or ceremony of
   commemorating the death of our Redeemer, in the use of bread and wine,
   as emblems of his flesh and blood, accompanied with approprite prayers
   and hymns.

   2. The act of giving thanks.
